        "goal_understanding": "The goal is to complete all goals in each level by matching the piece's shape, color, and rotation to the goal's requirements and stepping onto the goal cell. The player must navigate the grid, avoid walls, and manage stamina to complete all levels.",
        "mechanics_understanding": "The game is grid-based with four movement directions. The piece has three attributes: shape (0-5), color (orange, blue, green, red), and rotation (0\u00b0, 90\u00b0, 180\u00b0, 270\u00b0). Stepping on modifier tiles changes these attributes: shape changers cycle shape, color changers cycle color in order orange->blue->green->red->orange, and rotation changers rotate 90\u00b0 clockwise. Goals only activate when all three attributes match. Walls block movement and are indicated by blocked_directions. Stamina decreases by 1 per move; when it reaches 0, a life is lost and stamina resets. Losing all lives ends the game. The player must plan routes to reach modifiers and goals efficiently."
